        jTextArea1.setText("1. Login Frame\nLogin from use for the Inventory management system software opening and create account .if user no account then click Signup open new account frame. Login from use two option user name and password.\nUser name and password use from database. if user name or password any one is not correct then show the message wrong user name or password !!! and user name and password are correct the message show login successfully and open the Inventory  management system software home page. \n\n2. Signup\nIf needed more than one user then the administrator can create another user from Create Account Option. At the time of create account the administrator needed the below information.\n1.\tNew User Name\n2.\tNew Password\n3.\tConfirm Password\nInserted all information then click on create. Then the administrator shows a successfully created message and back button click going to login frame and login account.\n\n3.Home Page\nAfter login open home page. Home page has Inventory management system all options. All pages are visiting this home page. Home page is used for many buttons. Such as\n1.\tAdd item\n2.\tUpdate item\n3.\tDelete item\nIf you know about this Inventory Management System then clicked menu bar About option .File option are visiting Add, Update, Delete page and Exit this software system.  \n\n4. Add  Item\nAdd Item  page use for added product .Add  product page used take all product data and save this data to database.at first add  data  this Inventory this time take all document this Product  and this page add all documents. Student Information are added this page And go to Home page click Home Button . This page take this data.\n1.\tID\n2.\tName\n3.\tPrice\n4.\tDate\n5.\tImage\n\n5.Update Item\nIf Data need update then select id and change other option then click update button\nIf update is successful then view message box product update and if not update product then message show not update product.\nThen change product item and view other product in this page.\n\n6. Delete Product\nIf Data need Delete then select id and click Delete button and change first , next, previous  and last button click button select product. \nIf Delete is successful then view message box product Deleted and if not deleted then message show not deleted product.\nThen change product item and view other product in this page.\n\n\n\n\n\n");
